parameters.description: Time points of observations. From data column 'Time (days)'.
Observed nutrient concentration. From data column 'N_dat (Nutrient concentration in g C m^-3)'.
Observed phytoplankton concentration. From data column 'P_dat (Phytoplankton concentration in g C m^-3)'.
Observed zooplankton concentration. From data column 'Z_dat (Zooplankton concentration in g C m^-3)'.
Log of maximum phytoplankton growth rate (V_max, day^-1). A typical biological range for V_max is [0.5, 2.5].
Log of half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake (K_N, g C m^-3). A typical biological range for K_N is [0.05, 0.5].
Log of maximum zooplankton grazing rate (g_max, day^-1). A typical biological range for g_max is [0.4, 2.0].
Log of half-saturation constant for grazing (K_P, g C m^-3). A typical biological range for K_P is [0.1, 0.5].
Logit of zooplankton assimilation efficiency (beta, dimensionless). Beta must be between 0 and 1.
Log of phytoplankton linear mortality rate (m_P, day^-1). A typical biological range for m_P is [0.01, 0.1].
Log of zooplankton metabolic loss/excretion rate (l_Z, day^-1). A typical biological range for l_Z is [0.05, 0.2].
Log of zooplankton quadratic mortality rate (m_Z, (g C m^-3)^-1 day^-1). This parameter is highly system-dependent.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model on Nutrient observations.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model on Phytoplankton observations.
Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model on Zooplankton observations.
